FABS: // arg >= 0 to avoid -0 as a result of this instruction
			// as a fp number, it has to exist (by IEEE 754):
			// lets say x is given
			// x: 0000 0000 0000 0000
			// x=-x yields:
			// x: 1000 0000 0000 0000
			// whose exponent & significand are equal to 0
			// thus, x = -0
			// FIXME: When implementing arbitrary-precision numbers,
			// FIXME: think about mathematically accurate R encodings.
